# Format Detection Reference

Extended frame-name mapping, CUSTOM format handling, and edge cases for retro-analysis.

---

## Known Format Mappings

### Start / Stop / Continue (SSC)

Accepted frame name variants:
- Start, Stop, Continue
- Start doing, Stop doing, Keep doing
- Do more, Do less, Keep
- More of, Less of, Same
- Begin, Stop, Continue

Semantic mapping:
- Start / Do more / Begin → improvement opportunities, new ideas
- Stop / Do less → pain points, friction, things harming the team
- Continue / Keep / Same → what's working

---

### What Went Well / What Didn't / Actions (WWW)

Accepted frame name variants:
- What went well, What didn't go well, Actions
- Went well, Improve / Delta / Change, Actions / Next steps
- Positives, Negatives, Improvements
- + / Δ / → (symbol-only frames)
- Good, Bad, Ugly (rare but real)

Semantic mapping:
- What went well / Positives → what's working
- What didn't / Improve / Delta → pain points
- Actions / Next steps / Improvements → commitments

Note: When frames use symbols only (+ / Δ), treat as WWW and flag as CUSTOM for output labelling.

---

### 4Ls (Liked / Learned / Lacked / Longed for)

Accepted frame name variants:
- Liked, Learned, Lacked, Longed for
- Liked, Learned, Lacked, Wished
- Loved, Learned, Lacked, Longed

Semantic mapping:
- Liked → what's working, morale signals
- Learned → insights, process discoveries
- Lacked → pain points, missing resources or clarity
- Longed for → aspirations, systemic gaps, sometimes escalation fodder

Note: Lacked and Longed for often together reveal the delta between team capability and team need. When both are rich, they frequently surface systemic impediment candidates.

---

### Mad / Sad / Glad (MSG)

Accepted frame name variants:
- Mad, Sad, Glad
- Frustrated, Disappointed, Happy
- Angry, Concerned, Positive
- 😠 😢 😊 (emoji-only frames)

Semantic mapping:
- Mad / Frustrated / Angry → high-friction pain points; often higher-severity signal than equivalent SSC stickies
- Sad / Disappointed / Concerned → moderate friction, unmet expectations, erosion signals
- Glad / Happy / Positive → what's working

Caution: MSG formats tend to produce more emotionally charged language. Do not soften or normalise this. Report the register as-is. The emotional intensity is data.

