## CUSTOM Format Handling

When frame names do not match any known format:

**Step 1: Attempt semantic mapping**
If the frame name is interpretable (e.g. "Things slowing us down", "What surprised us", "Elephants in the room"), map it to the nearest semantic category and note the mapping explicitly:
> Frame "Elephants in the room" interpreted as: pain points / unspoken friction. Mapping is inferred — coach should confirm.

**Step 2: If semantic mapping fails, treat as unstructured**
If frame names are opaque (e.g. "Blue", "Group 1", no names at all), treat the entire board as unstructured. Apply the generic evidence model: look for repetition, clustering, and explicit language rather than relying on frame semantics.

**Step 3: Flag clearly**
Always note CUSTOM in the format detection header. Note which frames were successfully mapped and which were not.

---

## Edge Cases

**Hybrid boards:** Some teams use SSC for one section and add a freeform "Other" or "Parking lot" frame. Treat the structured frames with the relevant format logic and treat the freeform frame as unstructured content. Do not discard it — parking lot content often contains the most significant impediments.

**Duplicate frames:** Some exports contain the same frame name twice (facilitator error, split-screen boards). Merge content from both frames under that category and note the duplication.

**Unlabelled stickies outside frames:** Common in Miro exports where stickies were placed on the canvas rather than inside a frame. Treat as LOW signal unless content is clearly part of a theme. Note their presence in S7 / M6 ambiguity section.

**Empty frames:** A frame with a heading but no stickies may indicate a topic the team avoided or ran out of time for. Flag as a potential avoidance signal in coaching observations if the empty frame is a negative-feedback category (e.g. empty "What didn't go well" alongside rich positive frames).

**Screenshot-derived or OCR input:** If input quality is degraded (truncated words, garbled text, unclear frame boundaries), note this in Signal Quality and apply conservative evidence standards. Do not reconstruct what stickies "probably" said.
